So-Cal Churros
  --Cook's Country
Dough:
2 c water
2 tbsp unsalted butter
2 tbsp sugar
1 tsp vanilla
1/2 tsp salt
2 c (10oz) ap flour
2 large eggs
2 qt oil

Line rimmed baking sheet with parchment paper and spray with vegetable oil spray. Combine water, butter, sugar, vanilla, and salt in large saucepan and bring to boil over medium high heat. Remove from heat; add flour all at once and stir with rubber spatula until well combined, with no streaks of flour remaining. Transfer dough to bowl of stand mixer fitted with paddle and mix on low until cooled slightly, ~1 min. Add eggs, increase speed to medium, and beat until fully incorporated, ~1 min. Transfer warm dough to piping bag fitted with 5/8" closed star pastry tip. Pipe 18 (6") lengths of dough onto prepared sheet, using scissors to snip dough at tip. Refrigerate, uncovered, for at least 15 min or up to 1 hr. Adjust oven rack to middle position and heat to 200F. Set wire rack in another rimmed baking sheet and place in oven. Line large plate with triple layer of paper towels. Add oil to dutch oven until it measures ~ 1 1/2" deep and heat over medium high heat to 375F. Gently drop 6 churros into hot oil and fry until dark golden brown on all sides, ~6 min, turning frequently for even cooking. Adjust burner, if necessary, to maintain oil temp between 350-375F. Transfer churros to paper towl lined plate for 30s to drain off excess oil, then transfer to wire rack in oven. Return oil to 375F and repeat with remainin dough in 2 batches.

Chocolate Sauce:
3/4 c heavy cream
4 oz semisweet chocolate chips
pinch salt
1/4 tsp vanilla

Microwave cream, chocolate chips, and salt in bowl at 50% power, stirring occasionally, until melted, ~2 min. Stir in vanilla until smooth.

Coating:
1/2 c (3 1/2oz) sugar
3/4 tsp cinnamon

Combine in shallow dish. Roll churros in mixture, tapping gently to remove excess. Transfer to a platter and serve with warm chocolate sauce.
